<TITLE> Justices Rahman, Aziz take oath Sunday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 5 (bdnews24.com)  The newly-appointed judges of the Appellate Division of Supreme Court, justices Shah Abu Nayeem Mominur Rahman and Md Abdul Aziz, will take oath Sunday. Chief justice MM Ruhul Amin will administer the oath to office at 10:30am. Their appointments were gazetted Thursday. President Zillur Rahman appointed them Wednesday in line with recommendations of the Supreme Judicial Commission. Their appointments are believed to fast-track the hearing of the appeal in the case involving the assassination of independence leader Sheikh Mujibur Rahman. The commission recommended appointment of four High Court judges to Appellate Division on Oct. 16 last year, The judges are Justice Rahman, Justice Aziz, Justice Md Abdul Quddus and Justice Bijan Kumar Das. Justice Quddus retired on Jan. 14. Born on Nov. 11, 1944 at Gazipur, Justice Rahman was appointed judge to the High Court Division on June 1, 1996. He will retire on Nov. 24, 2011. Justice Aziz was born on Jan. 1, 1943 at Jessore and appointed to the High Court as a judge on April 27, 1998. He will retire on Dec. 31 this year. bd
